comment.TEXT: I absolutely love it even though I think some lords are a bit unbalanced.  If you read the rules it will feel a little clunky but I don't feel it when playing.  The art is amazing and the materials are of good quality.

name.TEXT: Betrayal at House on the Hill

comment.TEXT: I love the cheesiness of the whole horror movie setting.  The 50 scenarios feel diverse and fresh when you haven't played them before. I don't like that the game can take anywhere from 30 to 90 minutes and that the character markers keep falling off.
It feels like it is just a tweak away from being a good game. Winning does not feel particularly satisfying because once you get a solid dungeon it's easy mode.

Awesome castle building game.  I love how the strategic elements blend in with the silliness of building a castle that makes no sense.  Can be overwhelming to pick the room values when being the Master Builder, otherwise an absolute favorite.
